Course:  CMSC495 - Trends and Projects in Computer Science
Project: Splatter - Team 1
Author:  Michael Songy
Date:    10/15/2011
Platform:
 PostgreSQL 9.1
 Ubuntu 11.10

1. Purpose:
Database for the Splatter application.

2. Configuration Notes:
- Ubuntu 11.10
- PostgreSQL 9.1

3. Files included:
	README - This text file
	scripts - directory containing database creation scripts
	scripts/create_entity_tables.postgresql - script for creating the
		Splatter entity tables
	scripts/create_functions.postgresql - script for creating the
		stored function interface to the Splatter database
	scripts/setup.postgresql - top-level database creation script

4. To create the database:
	1. Create a new Linux user:
		sudo adduser splatter
	2. Create a new PostgreSQL user with database and role creation
	   rights:
		su postgres
		createuser splatter
		exit
	3. Create a new PostgreSQL database with the new user as owner:
		su postgres
		createdb -O splatter splatter
		exit
	4. Give the new user access to the scripts directory and contents
	5. Login as the newly created linux user:
		su splatter
	6. Change into the scripts directory, and then run psql:
		cd <location of scripts directory>/scripts
		psql
	7. At the psql prompt, run the setup script:
		\i setup.postgresql
